The paper focuses on managing large spatial datasets using a distributed computing infrastructure, which falls under the scope of database systems (cs.DB) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of Voronoi diagram as a partitioning and indexing technique suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The scalability and efficiency aspects of the proposed approach make it relevant to the sub-category of distributed systems (cs.Distributed) and spatial indexing (cs.SI).
